text: Henry Holden (1596–1662) was an English theologian. Henry Holden may also refer to: * Henry Holden (police officer) (1823–1900), English chief constable and cricketer * H. J. Holden (1859–1926), Australian businessman * Henry Smith Holden (1887–1963), British botanist ==See also== *Harry Holden (disambiguation)
